@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@showTimeId = 019d9bfc-8906-7623-8706-b3216a756417
@movieId = 019d9bfc-88eb-72e0-a5bb-e90161c15912
@screenId = 019d9bfc-88f0-7713-a762-90030a334093
@cinemaId = 019d9bfc-88e8-7867-83cd-1876f359738d

### 1) Get all showtimes
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/showtimes

### 2) Get showtimes with filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/showtimes?cinemaId={{cinemaId}}&movieId={{movieId}}&status=Upcoming

### 3) Get paged showtimes
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/showtimes/paged?pageNumber=1&pageSize=10&sortBy=startat&sortDirection=asc

### 4) Get paged showtimes by date
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/showtimes/paged?pageNumber=1&pageSize=10&date=2026-04-17&sortBy=startat&sortDirection=asc

### 5) Get showtime dropdown
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/showtimes/dropdown?maxItems=20&status=Upcoming

### 6) Get showtime detail by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/showtimes/{{showTimeId}}

### Realtime guide (SignalR)
# 1. Fetch snapshot first:
#    GET {{baseUrl}}/api/showtimes/{{showTimeId}}
# 2. Open SignalR connection to:
#    {{baseUrl}}/hubs/tickets
# 3. After connected, invoke hub method:
#    SubscribeShowTime(showTimeId)
# 4. Listen for server event:
#    ticket-status-changed
# 5. Merge delta payload (ticketId/ticketCode/status) into seat map UI state.

### 7) Add showtime
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/showtimes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "movieId": "{{movieId}}",
  "screenId": "{{screenId}}",
  "startAt": "2026-04-20T12:30:00+00:00",
  "correlationId": "sample-add-showtime"
}

### 8) Start showtime
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/showtimes/{{showTimeId}}/start

### 9) Complete showtime
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/showtimes/{{showTimeId}}/complete

### 10) Cancel showtime
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/showtimes/{{showTimeId}}/cancel
